author: Inside Edition
description: Charlie Kirk's accused assassin made his first in-person court appearance. Tyler Robinson sat between his attorneys, smiling and chatting with them as he awaited the judge. Robinson was brought to court under intense security. Inside the courtroom, an armed officer stood watch. Kirk's widow, Erika, spoke out in a new interview with CBS News Editor-in-Chief Bari Weiss and had harsh words for those who celebrated her husband's assassination.
title: Charlie Kirk's Alleged Assassin, Tyler Robinson, Appears In Court

author: Inside Edition
description: Singer Charlie Puth took to social media to complain to Elon Musk over his rocket launched. The popstar, who is preparing to be a first-time dad and gearing up for his national anthem performance at the Super Bowl said the "sonic booms have gotten progressively louder." SpaceX issued this disclaimer about Wednesday's launch: "Residents of nearby counties, including those in Santa Barbara, may have heard one or more sonic booms during the launch depending on weather conditions."
title: Singer Charlie Puth Calls Out SpaceX's Loud Rocket Launches

author: Inside Edition
description: Taylor Swift appeared on "The Late Show with Stephen Colbert" in a sculptural dress by designer David Koma and received a rousing standing ovation. She accessorized with a vintage 18-carat gold necklace and her eye-popping wedding ring. Swift revealed that during the Eras Tour, she had the stomach flu multiple times but still went on stage. She also compared her engagement to Travis Kelce to regaining control of her master tapes for her albums.
title: Taylor Swift Stuns In Burgundy Dress On Late Show With Steven Colbert

author: Inside Edition
description: A witness was in tears at the trial of art dealer Brian Walshe, who is accused of murdering and dismembering his wife, Ana Walshe. Alissa Kirby said she and her close friend, Ana, had a heart-to-heart about the stresses in Ana's marriage three days before she was last seen alive. Jurors heard testimony that Brian was making $60,000 a year while Ana was earning five times more. Brian pled guilty to improperly disposing of his wife's body, but he maintains he did not kill her.
title: Ana Walshe's Friend Testifies At Brian Walshe's Murder Trial

author: Inside Edition
description: University of Michigan football coach Sherrone Moore has been fired from his $30 million job, accused of cheating on his wife, and was being held in mental health protective custody. In a statement, the university said "credible evidence was found that Coach Moore engaged in an inappropriate relationship with a staff member. U-M maintains zero tolerance for such behavior.”
title: Shocking Accusations Emerge About College Football Coach Sherrone Moore

author: Inside Edition
description: When police arrived at the scene, they found condiments and cheese left out in the open, and food still cooking, but no employees.
title: Why Was This Hardee's Restaurant Completely Empty? #shorts

description: After eating the food they Doordashed to their Indiana home, Marc Cardin says his wife started coughing before throwing up. When Cardin watched the footage from the doorbell camera, he noticed the driver spraying something that he believed was pepper spray right on the bag.
title: Did  Doordash Driver Pepper Spray A Food Order? #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Cosmetic injections are one of our biggest beauty obsessions, but what could be in that syringe? Health officials across America are warning of a rise in unlicensed operators injecting cheap, counterfeit drugs shipped in from overseas, and the results can be devastating. But just how common is this? Two Inside Edition investigative producers went undercover to a New Jersey med spa for a Botox appointment, but their so-called doctor wasn't really a doctor at all.
title: Inside Edition Exposes Man Injecting Botox Without A Medical License

title: Volunteer Pilots Save 40 Animals From Euthanasia #shorts
